# Cursor Rules for AI Lecture Materials

## Documentation Style Guidelines

- **No emojis**: Do not use emojis in any documentation files (.md, .txt, etc.)
- **No em-dashes**: Use regular hyphens (-) instead of em-dashes (—) or en-dashes (–)
- **Plain text formatting**: Keep documentation clean and professional without decorative characters

## When Editing Documentation

- Remove any emojis found in markdown files
- Replace em-dashes (—) with regular hyphens (-)
- Replace en-dashes (–) with regular hyphens (-)
- Maintain consistent, professional tone throughout

